    <H1>CVS details</H1><DIV class="s1">
      <P>
	Our CVS repository is mounted at SourceForge.	
      </P>
      <P>
	See SourceForge's <A href="http://sourceforge.net/cvs/?group_id=43962">page</A> for CVS configuration details.  There are multiple modules.  See <A href="http://cvs.sourceforge.net/cgi-bin/viewcvs.cgi/jesktop/">page</A> for the module names.  They will all have to be placed relatively next to each other in a directory for building to work.  We use Ant (see below) to build the apps.
      </P>            
    </DIV>
    <H1>A word about Ant</H1><DIV class="s1">
      <P>
	Jesktop uses Ant for a platform neutral building.  What doesn't nowadays?  It wants to use it's own ant, not the one you may have installed.  <STRONG>As such it needs two things from you before starting:</STRONG>
      </P>	
      <OL>
        <LI>
          Environmental variable JAVA_HOME set to the correct directory.  Sun describe this in their Java installation procedures.
        </LI>
        <LI>
          Environmental variable PATH to have JAVA_HOME/bin as one of it's colon or semi colon separated entries.
        </LI>
      </OL>      	
    </DIV>    
